/* Amnesty's controversial visits to the camp of the People's Mujahedin in Albania */  Added another citation from another group condemning Amnesty for conducting research at a camp where torture and other abuses take place.
Complaint about new subsection added and then removed by a biased moderator.
The moderator censoring this information needs to be investigated for bias. He allows a ton of criticism of AI for reporting on Israel but not on this topic.

1. The camp that AI visited to do its research is mentioned in the Channel4news documentary as a place where human rights occurs. 2. NejatNGO is a community representing the families of members held against their will in the camp.
